eNCA speaks to presidential spokesperson Vincent Magwenya. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Presidency spokesperson Vincent Magwenya has accused UDM leader Bantu Holomisa of misleading the public. He adds comments that President Cyril Ramaphosa’s 2017 ANC presidential campaign may have used public funds are baseless and vindictive. READ: Meyiwa Murder Trial | Ramaphosa refutes claims by Teffo Magwenya says the CR17 campaign was not a public entity and there were no public funds used. Meanwhile, Ramaphosa will not appear before the impeachment inquiry into the Public Protector as per Holomisa's suggestion. Watch the full interview in the video above. 